<quantity box="[673,753,1249,1271]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="56" pageNumber="1015" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
. Form: As in 
<figureCitation box="[895,980,1248,1271]" captionStart="Figs 342-345" captionStartId="113.[151,191,1528,1550]" captionTargetBox="[154,1061,201,1516]" captionTargetId="figure@113.[153,1061,201,1516]" captionTargetPageId="113" captionText="Figs 342-345: Habitus; (342) Pujoliclerus dexus; (343) P. flavidus; (344) P. lasiosus; (345) P. melonius." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746834" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746834/files/figure.png" pageId="56" pageNumber="1015">Fig. 345</figureCitation>
. Color: Cranium testaceous, epicranium with narrow medial line; antenna bicolorous, mostly brown, capitulum partially yellow; prothorax bicolorous, venter and pronotal anterior angles yellow, pronotal disc mostly black; pterothorax and abdomen brown; legs mostly yellow, prothoracic tibiae and femora infuscated; tarsi light brown; elytra mostly dark brown, posterior 1/2 of epipleural suture and elytral apex testaceous. Head: Cranium coarsely punctate; antenna (
<figureCitation box="[436,511,1424,1447]" captionStart="Figs 1-27" captionStartId="70.[151,191,1302,1324]" captionTargetBox="[155,1057,207,1268]" captionTargetId="figure@70.[155,1058,207,1283]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="Figs 1-27: Antennae; (1) Aphelocerus nodus; (2) A. copanus; (3) A. magnipannus; (4) A. yoro; (5) A. sparicapillus; (6) A. tigra. (7) A. nolus; (8) A. ligulus; (9) Perilypus schusteri; (10) P. apunctus; (11) P. virgulatus; (12) P. izabal; (13) P. alpinus; (14) Cregya fuscomacula; (15) Phonius versus; (16) Pujoliclerus ariquemes; (17) Pelonium falcatum; (18) Pujoliclerus cnecostus; (19) P. trunculus. (20) P. sentus; (21) P. testudinatus; (22) P. catie; (23) P. flavidus; (24) P. convexus; (25) P. meloinus; (26) P. mexicoensis; (27) P. tuxtlas." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746746/files/figure.png" pageId="56" pageNumber="1015">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
) capitate, most funicular antennomeres triangular, 6 
<superScript attach="none" box="[1046,1059,1421,1435]" fontSize="6" pageId="56" pageNumber="1015">th</superScript>
antennomeres robustly expanded; capitular antennomeres 8 and 9 triangular, antennomere 10 ovoid; eyes large, coarsely facetted, eye narrower than frons (EW/FW 23/27). Thorax: Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[355,444,1513,1535]" captionStart="Figs 134-152" captionStartId="77.[151,191,1476,1498]" captionTargetBox="[183,1049,204,1454]" captionTargetId="figure@77.[152,1060,199,1462]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="Figs 134-152: Pronota; (134) Pujoliclerus catie; (135) P. mexicoensis; (136) P. convexus; (137) P. testudinatus; (138) Madoniella selvanegra; (139) Cregya entrerios; (140) Pujoliclerus trunculus; (141) P. sentus; (142) P. meloinus; (143) Sicamus suprus; (144) Nepsudia guenda; (145) Nanoclerus fuscus; (146) Topainca pachacutii; (147) Eurycaulis anaxeis; (148) Kataspinula puebla; (149) Madoniella muralla; (150) M. nota; (151) M. acicula; (152) M. baja." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746760" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746760/files/figure.png" pageId="56" pageNumber="1015">Fig. 139</figureCitation>
) transverse (PW/PL 64/60), disc finely punctate at middle, coarsely punctate at sides, lateral tubercles well developed; elytra sculptured with striae of asetiferous punctures that diminish at elytral 1/2 (EL/EW 180/50). Abdomen: Pygidium transverse 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[364,371,211,233]" pageId="57" pageNumber="1016">/</emphasis>
scutiform, posterior margin deeply incised; aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 249-254" captionStartId="91.[151,191,1289,1311]" captionTargetBox="[155,1061,201,1276]" captionTargetId="figure@91.[155,1061,201,1276]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="Figs 249-254: Aedeagi; (249) Pujoliclerus catie; (250) P. dexus; (251) P. meloinus; (252) P. mexicoensis (253) P. testudinatus (254) P. trunculus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746788" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746788/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="1016">Fig. 251.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
